    "explanation": "<p>Change in momentum is given by the area under the $F-t$ graph.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mfkucf9r/1fe81217-b264-4875-b423-48a2687e1697/fea6adf0-920a-11f0-bd90-83ebe92be510/file-jaoe38c1mfkucf9s.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mfkucf9r/1fe81217-b264-4875-b423-48a2687e1697/fea6adf0-920a-11f0-bd90-83ebe92be510/file-jaoe38c1mfkucf9s.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"MHT CET (PCB) 2025 9th April Morning Shift Physics - Laws of Motion Question 1 English Explanation\">$$ \\begin{aligned} &amp; \\text { Area }=5 \\times 0.4+10 \\times 0.6 \\\\ = &amp; 2+6=8 \\mathrm{~N}-\\mathrm{s} \\\\ \\therefore &amp; \\mathrm{mv}=8 \\mathrm{~N}-\\mathrm{s} \\\\ \\therefore &amp; v=\\frac{8}{2}=4 \\mathrm{~m} / \\mathrm{s} \\end{aligned} $$</p>",
